# Database / Prisma

Follow `docs/DATABASE.md` and `docs/SECURITY.md`.

## Must

- UUID PKs; `tenant_id` on tenant-owned tables; composite indexes leading with `tenant_id`.
- Audit fields: `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`.
- Soft deletes via `deleted_at` where recovery/audit matters.
- Version prompts, workflow definitions, and similar configs — never silent overwrite.
- Store `secret_ref`, never raw secrets.
- Knowledge chunks: embeddings + ACL metadata; queries always filter tenant + ACL.
- Forward-only migrations; repository helpers enforce tenant scope.

## Never

Duplicate source-of-truth columns · client-trusted `tenant_id` filters as sole security · Prisma in Domain layer.
